               <msContents>
                  <summary>Paulus and Apis order Horsois to repay a large debt, and they make an oblique threat about calling in a soldier to collect the sum if he does not comply. In addition, Horsois is to tell Demetrios to send the money which Demetrios owes, and there is another mancing reference to soldiers before  the papyrus breaks off.</summary>
