   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>"To Horsois, their brother, Paulus and Apis: may you prosper.;Hasten to repay the hundred talents to Dios, and take from him your cheirograph with all security. See to it that you do not neglect to give him the money for which you will receive your cheirograph. In fact, we have not given your cheirograph to a soldier, so that you might be troubled. Do you therefore not neglect to give it (i.e. the money) to Dios who brings you my letter.;Tell Demetrios: &amp;apos;Hasten to send the man&amp;apos;s money, now that he has become an epitropos, so that you may not be summoned by the soldiers . . . &amp;apos; ";;Verso: "Sent to Horsois from Apis and Paulus."</ab>
         </div>
